# 💀 Dead Letter Queue (DLQ)

## 📖 Definition

A Dead Letter Queue (DLQ) is a special queue that stores messages that cannot be processed successfully after all retry attempts have been exhausted.

Instead of blocking the system, failed messages are moved to the DLQ for later investigation.

---

## 🎯 Use Cases

* Invalid message format
* Missing required fields
* Corrupted data
* Permanent business rule violations

---

## 📊 Flow

```text
Producer
   |
   v
Main Queue
   |
   v
Consumer
   |
   +--> Retry #1
   +--> Retry #2
   +--> Retry #3
   |
   v
  DLQ
```

---

## Example Message

```json
{
  "orderId": null,
  "amount": 100
}
```

Message repeatedly fails validation and is moved to DLQ.

---

## ✅ Benefits

* Prevents poison messages from blocking queues
* Preserves failed messages
* Enables troubleshooting and replay

---

## ⚙️ Common Technologies

| Technology        | DLQ Support          |
| ----------------- | -------------------- |
| Azure Service Bus | Built-in DLQ         |
| RabbitMQ          | Dead Letter Exchange |
| Kafka             | Dead Letter Topic    |
| Amazon SQS        | DLQ                  |

