# 🚦 Circuit Breaker Pattern

## 📖 Definition

A Circuit Breaker prevents requests from continuously hitting an unhealthy service.

Instead of repeatedly calling a failing service, the circuit "opens" and immediately returns an error or fallback response.

---

## 🎯 Use Cases

* Downstream service outage
* Slow APIs
* Database failures
* Third-party service failures

---

## 🔄 Circuit Breaker States

| State     | Description                                   |
| --------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| Closed    | Requests flow normally                        |
| Open      | Requests fail immediately                     |
| Half-Open | Limited requests are allowed to test recovery |

---

### 🟢 Closed State

```text
Client ---> Service
```

Service is healthy.

---

### 🔴 Open State

```text
Client ---> Circuit Breaker
               |
               X
            Service
```

Service is unhealthy.

No requests are sent.

---

### 🟡 Half-Open State

```text
Client ---> Circuit Breaker
               |
               v
            Service
```

A small number of requests test whether the service has recovered.

---

## ✅ Benefits

* Prevents cascading failures
* Protects downstream services
* Improves overall system stability

