# 🧠 Interview Tips

### Retry

✅ Use for transient failures

✅ Use exponential backoff

✅ Add jitter

---

### DLQ

✅ Never lose failed messages

✅ Investigate and replay later

✅ Common in event-driven systems

---

### Circuit Breaker

✅ Prevent cascading failures

✅ Protect downstream services

✅ Common in microservices architectures

---

# 🎯 Key Takeaway

**Retry** handles temporary failures.

**DLQ** handles unrecoverable message failures.

**Circuit Breaker** protects the system from cascading failures.

Together, these patterns form the foundation of resilience in modern distributed systems and microservices architectures.
